14· profectioni: the dative with abhorreo is peculiar to this place, and the ablative without a prepo- sition is not common. lt may be a kind of construction according to the sense. — cetera sollemnia: i.e. those used at public sales of booty. —bona, etc.: a part of the booty was apparently so described at the sale.

2. omissam: attracted to agree- ment with originem, though it, as well as crevisse, belongs with moris. — titulus: the notice of sale in which the property to be sold was enumerated. — hostiliter: i.e. as the property of an enemy, opposed to the peaceable character
